>> earlier the code we did has a major flow, we used batch gradient descent , means we are using our complete data for calculation of parameters hence very space insufficient
>> so rather then using the entire data we should use data in small batches and this is called miny batch descent

>> we have written the manual code for this but its not efficient 
>> so we use dataset and data loader classes given by the pytorch

>> dataset class loads the data and data loader make the batches of the loaded data 

>> inside the dataclass 
    inside __init__ we define how the data should be loaded from the memory
    __len__ tell the total no of rows and hence tells us what no of batches would be formed 
    __getitem__ returns the data at the given index

>> dataloader 
    first shuffles the indices and then make the batches of size decided earlier
    then we send this to our custom dataset class to the __getitem__ 
    in the end batch is returned to the main training loop 

>> till now all this work is sequential so we use workers feature for parralelly doing things
>> dataloadercontaines a feature called sampler which helps in randomizing the indices
>> now also we can make our custom sampler obviously Sequentialsamlpler and customsampler 
>> collate funstion specifies how to combine a list of indices to make a batch tensor   
 